reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sparkling Smiles All Around!
reviews.reviewText: These kids' toothbrushes are an absolute hit! From their playful designs to the gentle bristles, they make brushing a delightful experience for little ones. The vibrant colors and fun characters add an element of excitement, turning oral care into a positive daily routine. The ergonomic design ensures easy handling for tiny hands, promoting independence in brushing. The quality of the bristles is fantastic, effectively cleaning teeth without causing discomfort. Parents can rest easy knowing that their children are using a reliable and enjoyable toothbrush. These 5-star kids' toothbrushes contribute to bright smiles and healthy dental habits – a win-win for both kids and parents!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Purchased twice now!
reviews.reviewText: My twin boys love animals and animal based toothbrushes are a great way to encourage them into healthy brushing habits. I love these brushes because the price per toothbrush is excellent. The suction cups are fun for the kids to stick to counter tops. Each toothbrush has a plastic reusable cover over the head for travel. There are two kinds...some of the brushes have ones that just slide on and other brushes will have the kind with two halves that snap together. I prefer the latter for travel purposes. The bristles are very soft...perhaps a bit too soft. My kids tend to chew on the brush heads and they do wear out pretty quickly. But for the price, still worth it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great to Gift To Students in 3K and Pre-K
reviews.reviewText: As part of a lesson on self-care, I purchased these toothbrushes for my students. The brushes came with covers, so that was a plus. I did not imagine that my students would be so excited to brush their teeth and walked around the classroom showing everyone their new toothbrush. At dismissal, they excitedly showed their parents their toothbrush too. I'm sure it's not the best quality, but it serves its purpose and it helped to encouraged dental care for my little learners.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My younger girls go through so many toothbrushes. It is ridiculous. So I decided to buy them in bulk to same time, money, and maybe some sanity. These aren’t the best. The bristles flatten and fray really quickly. (Which is fine for me since the girls might get a month of use out of a toothbrush if I’m lucky.) The little suction cups on the bottom come off if they are playing with the toothbrushes (which my girls are). It also seems like a waste to have the covers on all the toothbrushes. They aren’t awful. They work. They are affordable. But they aren’t great. There are definitely better kid toothbrushes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars They're soft, but that's not exactly a compliment
reviews.reviewText: It's way too soft. I always feel like a toothbrush does needs some more sturdiness in order to do it's job. I gave it a good rating for traveling because each brush does come with a toothbrush protector. The other con is that the rubber in the bottom does not stick, so it's not possible for the toothbrush to stand well. Will not be purchasing in the future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my 2.5 year old.
reviews.reviewText: This is definitely a toddler tooth brush not a kids tooth brush, but that's why I bought it! The suction feature is great too, helps create even more independence in terms of putting it down. I love the variety and multipack. My toddler chews on her brushes the moment I look away so we go through them in a few weeks (3-4 weeks) which is fine because you're supposed to replace your tooth brush monthly anyways. Overall they're soft, cute, fit perfect in a toddler hands, and love the added cover for travel!
